1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:02,735
Julia:
<i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:02,737 --> 00:00:04,737
<i>At least it used to be,</i>

3
00:00:04,739 --> 00:00:06,739
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:06,741 --> 00:00:08,707
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:12,546 --> 00:00:15,180
<i>Invisible, indestructible,</i>

6
00:00:15,182 --> 00:00:16,682
<i>Inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:16,684 --> 00:00:18,684
We're trapped.

8
00:00:18,686 --> 00:00:21,487
Julia:
<i>We don't know where it</i>
<i>came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:21,489 --> 00:00:23,655
<i>But now that we're all trapped</i>
<i>under the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:23,657 --> 00:00:25,457
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:25,459 --> 00:00:29,028
What's wrong
with your mom?
She's a diabetic.

12
00:00:29,030 --> 00:00:30,195
Ollie:
<i>You want my water,</i>

13
00:00:30,197 --> 00:00:33,432
Angie: <i>Junior locked me</i>
<i>in his fallout shelter.</i>

14
00:00:33,434 --> 00:00:34,700
Junior's a cop now.

15
00:00:34,702 --> 00:00:36,702
Who's gonna
believe my word?
I do.

16
00:00:36,704 --> 00:00:37,703
We're just gonna
take what we want.

17
00:00:37,705 --> 00:00:39,271
No!

18
00:00:39,273 --> 00:00:39,805
Hey!

19
00:00:41,142 --> 00:00:43,776
Julia: <i>Joe and norrie touched</i>
<i>the dome together.</i>

20
00:00:43,778 --> 00:00:46,445
Big jim:
<i>I'm offering you my word.</i>

21
00:00:46,447 --> 00:00:48,313
Junior rennie will
never touch you again.

22
00:00:48,315 --> 00:00:49,348
Junior:
Dad.

23
00:00:49,350 --> 00:00:50,416
Angie?

24
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:01,126
Joe...

25
00:01:02,195 --> 00:01:04,363
Joe...

26
00:01:04,365 --> 00:01:05,431
Joe!

27
00:01:07,333 --> 00:01:09,501
norrie.

28
00:01:09,503 --> 00:01:10,769
Hi.

29
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:13,372
Welcome to my room.

30
00:01:13,374 --> 00:01:15,374
I want you to come
with me to the dome.

31
00:01:15,376 --> 00:01:17,242
So we can figure
all this out.

32
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:19,445
See how we're really
connected to it.

33
00:01:19,447 --> 00:01:21,513
Just because dodee's
gadget thing beeped at us

34
00:01:21,515 --> 00:01:25,184
Something happened
when we both touched it.

35
00:01:25,186 --> 00:01:26,685
It was like we had
powers or something.

36
00:01:26,687 --> 00:01:28,520
Don't you think
that's amazing?

37
00:01:28,522 --> 00:01:31,490
It's not exactly
the word I'd use.

38
00:01:31,492 --> 00:01:34,259
Well, you should.

39
00:01:34,261 --> 00:01:36,662
Let's go see if we can
talk to it or something.

40
00:01:36,664 --> 00:01:38,397
See what
the dome wants,

41
00:01:38,399 --> 00:01:39,731
And convince it
to go away.

42
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:42,334
Can I get my pants on first?

43
00:01:42,336 --> 00:01:44,203
Can I watch?

44
00:01:45,438 --> 00:01:47,573
Kidding.

45
00:01:49,175 --> 00:01:51,243
♪

46
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:23,408
No.

47
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:26,245
I'd like you to stay.

48
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:38,924
They will go away.

49
00:02:52,605 --> 00:02:54,306
Harriet.
Hi.

50
00:02:54,308 --> 00:02:55,307
Everything okay?

51
00:02:55,309 --> 00:02:56,508
I'm sorry,
I know it's early.

52
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:58,210
Do you have any yogurt?

53
00:02:58,212 --> 00:03:01,547
The food mart's emptied out
after the people raided it,

54
00:03:01,549 --> 00:03:03,582
And it's the only thing
I can keep down.

55
00:03:04,551 --> 00:03:06,485
Just a month
to go, huh?

56
00:03:06,487 --> 00:03:08,253
Six weeks.

57
00:03:08,255 --> 00:03:09,955
Greg's deployment
was gonna be over

58
00:03:09,957 --> 00:03:11,623
So he could be home
when the baby's born,

59
00:03:11,625 --> 00:03:13,625
But with this thing...

60
00:03:13,627 --> 00:03:15,561
I don't know.

61
00:03:15,563 --> 00:03:18,230
Oh. Hi.

62
00:03:18,232 --> 00:03:20,399
Morning.

63
00:03:20,401 --> 00:03:23,502
Barbie, this is
my neighbor harriet.

64
00:03:23,504 --> 00:03:25,237
I think I have
that yogurt.

65
00:03:26,673 --> 00:03:28,707
I'm sorry.

66
00:03:36,349 --> 00:03:37,482
Where are you
off to?

67
00:03:37,484 --> 00:03:38,684
Running away?

68
00:03:38,686 --> 00:03:40,385
Half the town
going nuts yesterday,

69
00:03:40,387 --> 00:03:42,521
That wasn't a fluke.
So...

70
00:03:42,523 --> 00:03:44,590
Linda could still
use my help.

71
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:55,267
I told you last night

72
00:03:55,269 --> 00:03:56,768
To stay away from
angie, didn't I?
I'm sorry.

73
00:03:56,770 --> 00:03:58,770
I... I went to her room
just to talk to her.

74
00:03:58,772 --> 00:03:59,771
Please don't do this.

75
00:03:59,773 --> 00:04:01,240
Come on, please, don't.

76
00:04:01,242 --> 00:04:02,674
She... She can hear.

77
00:04:02,676 --> 00:04:05,277
Oh, I'm embarrassing you?
Huh?

78
00:04:05,279 --> 00:04:07,312
The guy who locks
a girl up in a shelter?
I had to.

79
00:04:07,314 --> 00:04:08,480
The dome was
making her sick.

80
00:04:08,482 --> 00:04:10,482
You're the one
who's sick!

81
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:18,624
Please don't say that.

82
00:04:18,626 --> 00:04:21,326
You have to leave.

83
00:04:21,328 --> 00:04:24,529
This is my home.
Where else am I supposed to go?

84
00:04:24,531 --> 00:04:25,998
Anywhere but here.

85
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,801
And if you ever
so much as get near angie,

86
00:04:29,803 --> 00:04:32,771
I'll make you sorry.

87
00:04:32,773 --> 00:04:35,274
I promise.

88
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:38,677
Dad, don't.

89
00:04:43,883 --> 00:04:45,284
He <i>is</i> crazy.

90
00:04:50,023 --> 00:04:53,025
Well, now he won't be a problem
for either of us.

91
00:04:53,993 --> 00:04:56,361
You look tired.

92
00:04:56,363 --> 00:04:58,597
I know I am.

93
00:04:58,599 --> 00:05:01,633
More than welcome to stay here.

94
00:05:01,635 --> 00:05:03,368
You just want to make sure

95
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:04,903
I don't tell everyone
what junior did.

96
00:05:04,905 --> 00:05:07,639
No, I...

97
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:09,708
I'm going home to my brother.

98
00:05:12,612 --> 00:05:14,913
After I say good-bye to rose.

99
00:05:16,783 --> 00:05:17,949
Where did,
um...

100
00:05:18,952 --> 00:05:22,020
I don't know if you heard
about lester coggins,

101
00:05:22,022 --> 00:05:24,556
But no one took over
the mortuary since he passed,

102
00:05:24,558 --> 00:05:27,993
So linda had to leave rose...

103
00:05:27,995 --> 00:05:29,561
In the sweetbriar kitchen.

104
00:05:29,563 --> 00:05:30,862
What?

105
00:05:30,864 --> 00:05:31,963
I know it's a shame,

106
00:05:31,965 --> 00:05:33,865
But it's just until
she can get buried.

107
00:05:33,867 --> 00:05:35,600
Here.

108
00:05:37,403 --> 00:05:40,405
I want you to take this
and go see her.

109
00:05:40,407 --> 00:05:42,374
You have a key to the diner?

110
00:05:42,376 --> 00:05:43,775
Well, I'd better.

111
00:05:43,777 --> 00:05:45,877
I own the place.

112
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:50,115
I kept loaning rose money
over the years to keep it open.

113
00:05:50,117 --> 00:05:51,616
It just seemed silly

114
00:05:51,618 --> 00:05:55,620
After a while,
so I... Bought it.

115
00:05:57,390 --> 00:05:59,691
I know that she was
your friend, too.

116
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:05,897
Say good-bye for both of us.

117
00:06:19,812 --> 00:06:20,879
Thanks again, julia.

118
00:06:20,881 --> 00:06:22,647
Any time.

119
00:06:28,121 --> 00:06:30,389
Man:
Harriet!

120
00:06:31,457 --> 00:06:33,792
Honey!

121
00:06:33,794 --> 00:06:35,026
Come here.

122
00:06:35,028 --> 00:06:37,629
Greg?

123
00:06:37,631 --> 00:06:40,665
You're really here?

124
00:06:51,144 --> 00:06:53,979
I finally made it
home to you, baby.

125
00:06:55,648 --> 00:06:56,748
ah!

126
00:07:00,854 --> 00:07:03,955
Greg? Greg?

127
00:07:03,957 --> 00:07:05,490
Julia!

128
00:07:05,492 --> 00:07:06,725
Julia:
Harriet?
Julia!

129
00:07:06,727 --> 00:07:08,760
Anybody, help me, please!

130
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:10,195
Ah!
Julia:
I'm coming, sweetie.

131
00:07:10,197 --> 00:07:11,830
I got you.
I'm right here.

132
00:07:11,832 --> 00:07:13,765
it's okay.
It's okay.

133
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:15,033
It's just your water breaking.
No...

134
00:07:15,035 --> 00:07:16,168
It's too early!

135
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:18,770
Ah...
I touched the dome.

136
00:07:18,772 --> 00:07:20,772
I think it did something

137
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:22,507
To my baby.

138
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:50,569
You're the only deputy
that bothered to show up today.

139
00:07:53,239 --> 00:07:55,574
Where else am I gonna go?

140
00:07:59,579 --> 00:08:00,679
Barbie:
Junior.

141
00:08:00,681 --> 00:08:01,746
Hey.

142
00:08:04,684 --> 00:08:06,718
Anyone else wondering

143
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,553
What's gonna happen
next in this town?

144
00:08:08,555 --> 00:08:10,922
Yeah, well, we need
to deal with the dundees.

145
00:08:10,924 --> 00:08:13,124
Clint and waylon
killed rose yesterday.

146
00:08:13,126 --> 00:08:14,626
I went by their
place last night,

147
00:08:14,628 --> 00:08:16,261
But they're smart enough
not to go home.

148
00:08:16,263 --> 00:08:18,663
Let's go track 'em down.

149
00:08:18,665 --> 00:08:19,865
Junior, you stay on patrol.

150
00:08:19,867 --> 00:08:23,168
They're even thinking of
looting, you shut it down.

151
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:24,870
Okay, just let him go on patrol.

152
00:08:24,872 --> 00:08:26,972
I know the dundees; I might
be able to talk them down

153
00:08:26,974 --> 00:08:28,874
Without things
getting stupid.

154
00:08:28,876 --> 00:08:32,644
Uh, that's fine by me.

155
00:08:32,646 --> 00:08:34,279
All right, come on.

156
00:08:44,725 --> 00:08:46,525
Okay.

157
00:08:46,527 --> 00:08:48,527
Thank you, julia.

158
00:08:50,664 --> 00:08:51,897
You thought
you saw greg?

159
00:08:51,899 --> 00:08:53,632
I did see greg.

160
00:08:53,634 --> 00:08:55,667
He was waving to me.

161
00:08:55,669 --> 00:08:57,602
I thought it meant
that the dome was gone,

162
00:08:57,604 --> 00:08:59,871
And then when I went to him
and tried to touch him...

163
00:08:59,873 --> 00:09:01,606
He wasn't there.
I should've known

164
00:09:01,608 --> 00:09:02,841
It was too good to be...

165
00:09:04,878 --> 00:09:06,645
We should get you
to the clinic.

166
00:09:06,647 --> 00:09:07,879
Okay, let's take my car.

167
00:09:07,881 --> 00:09:09,881
Greg put a hospital
go bag in there.

168
00:09:09,883 --> 00:09:10,916
Okay.

169
00:09:10,918 --> 00:09:12,284
Let's go.

170
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:47,252
Rose.

171
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:59,264
Ben:
Who's in there?!

172
00:10:01,634 --> 00:10:03,802
Stay away from me!
Whoa, whoa!

173
00:10:03,804 --> 00:10:06,638
I'm not gonna hurt you.

174
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:07,639
Wait.

175
00:10:07,641 --> 00:10:10,108
You're joe's sister.

176
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:12,243
I'm ben. I'm friends
with your brother.

177
00:10:12,245 --> 00:10:14,145
Uh, is joe okay?

178
00:10:14,147 --> 00:10:16,214
Yeah, he's hanging
with his new girlfriend.

179
00:10:16,216 --> 00:10:19,117
Seriously, you don't need
to be stabby with me.

180
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:21,319
I just saw the door open
and wanted to make sure

181
00:10:21,321 --> 00:10:22,821
No one was
wrecking stuff again.

182
00:10:24,625 --> 00:10:26,825
Oh, damn.

183
00:10:26,827 --> 00:10:29,394
Is that rose?

184
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:40,639
Will you help me
with something?

185
00:10:40,641 --> 00:10:43,174
Ollie: Go on, folks,
take all you can carry.

186
00:10:43,176 --> 00:10:45,377
That well ain't running
out any time soon.

187
00:10:45,379 --> 00:10:47,879
Big jim:
So business is booming.

188
00:10:49,849 --> 00:10:53,284
That grin of yours is about
to cut the top of your head off.

189
00:10:53,286 --> 00:10:54,653
Well, town needed me.

190
00:10:54,655 --> 00:10:56,254
And I'm happy to help.

191
00:10:56,256 --> 00:10:58,256
Sure you are.

192
00:10:58,258 --> 00:11:00,358
Long as I keep you
stockpiled in propane.

193
00:11:02,428 --> 00:11:04,829
Just a capitalist.

194
00:11:04,831 --> 00:11:06,297
Like you, jim.

195
00:11:06,299 --> 00:11:08,700
But you didn't come
out here to chew the fat

196
00:11:08,702 --> 00:11:09,734
With your old pal.

197
00:11:09,736 --> 00:11:11,302
No.

198
00:11:11,304 --> 00:11:13,672
I came to bury the hatchet.

199
00:11:13,674 --> 00:11:15,373
You?

200
00:11:15,375 --> 00:11:16,841
Look, ollie.

201
00:11:16,843 --> 00:11:18,943
We can keep pissing
each other off

202
00:11:18,945 --> 00:11:20,311
Or we can get things done.

203
00:11:20,313 --> 00:11:22,247
Okay? Now, you got the water.

204
00:11:22,249 --> 00:11:26,851
We work together, we can get
this town here back on track,

205
00:11:26,853 --> 00:11:28,420
And our friends and neighbors
back on their feet.

206
00:11:28,422 --> 00:11:29,721
Good old big jim.

207
00:11:29,723 --> 00:11:31,256
Always thinking
of chester's mill.

208
00:11:31,258 --> 00:11:33,725
Well, it's
the right thing to do.

209
00:11:33,727 --> 00:11:35,794
Still...

210
00:11:35,796 --> 00:11:37,862
You sure about that
propane supply?

211
00:11:37,864 --> 00:11:40,331
Trust me, it won't run out.

212
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:45,904
But what I'm asking is...
Are you sure it's still yours?

213
00:11:49,141 --> 00:11:52,210
What the hell does that mean?

214
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:58,016
Sure was a nice new dawn
this morning, wasn't it?

215
00:12:11,097 --> 00:12:13,131
Anything?

216
00:12:13,133 --> 00:12:14,265
Yeah.

217
00:12:14,267 --> 00:12:15,467
You're really good at that.

218
00:12:15,469 --> 00:12:17,168
From the dome, joe.

219
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:18,336
Anything from the dome?

220
00:12:18,338 --> 00:12:20,371
I didn't feel anything,
like a seizure.

221
00:12:20,373 --> 00:12:21,806
Me neither.

222
00:12:21,808 --> 00:12:23,775
Unfortunately.

223
00:12:23,777 --> 00:12:26,344
Maybe we're going
about it all wrong.

224
00:12:26,346 --> 00:12:28,046
I-I mean, we've touched it.

225
00:12:28,048 --> 00:12:29,247
We've talked to it.

226
00:12:29,249 --> 00:12:30,248
Made out on it.

227
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:31,449
Which was awesome.

228
00:12:31,451 --> 00:12:33,251
But every single time
something has happened,

229
00:12:33,253 --> 00:12:36,321
It's been because we did
something different.

230
00:12:36,323 --> 00:12:38,156
Joe, I'm not
having sex with you

231
00:12:38,158 --> 00:12:39,457
For the first time
against the dome.

232
00:12:39,459 --> 00:12:40,792
I didn't mean that.

233
00:12:40,794 --> 00:12:42,827
Wait, but...
You want to do that?

234
00:12:42,829 --> 00:12:44,796
Focus.

235
00:12:44,798 --> 00:12:47,132
I'm just saying.

236
00:12:47,134 --> 00:12:48,399
Maybe we're trying
to get a response

237
00:12:48,401 --> 00:12:52,036
Maybe the real action isn't
along the perimeter.

238
00:12:52,038 --> 00:12:53,538
where else would it be?

239
00:12:56,342 --> 00:12:58,376
If the dome is like an atom,

240
00:12:58,378 --> 00:13:01,546
And these walls are-are
just electrons...

241
00:13:03,516 --> 00:13:07,385
...That means there has to be
a nucleus in the center of it.

242
00:13:07,387 --> 00:13:09,187
Which could be holding
it all together.

243
00:13:09,189 --> 00:13:11,055
Maybe that's where we should go.

244
00:13:12,424 --> 00:13:14,259
You're smart,
joe mcalister.

245
00:13:32,545 --> 00:13:34,112
What the hell is this, boomer?

246
00:13:34,114 --> 00:13:35,547
You better say
you somehow got lost

247
00:13:35,549 --> 00:13:37,315
On your way
to your damn cornfield!

248
00:13:37,317 --> 00:13:39,217
Gonna have to stop you
right there, mr. Rennie.

249
00:13:39,219 --> 00:13:40,552
Ollie says no one's allowed

250
00:13:40,554 --> 00:13:42,320
Inside but him.
Ollie?

251
00:13:42,322 --> 00:13:43,555
Yeah.
This is my property,

252
00:13:43,557 --> 00:13:46,357
Them keys ain't gonna
do you any good.

253
00:13:51,363 --> 00:13:53,865
Now, look here, boomer.

254
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:55,233
You get out of my way...

255
00:13:57,137 --> 00:13:59,170
You...

256
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:05,310
Mouthy townie bastard.

257
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:51,623
So what happens
after we catch waylon and clint?

258
00:14:51,625 --> 00:14:55,159
Put them in a cell.

259
00:14:55,161 --> 00:14:56,594
Then what?

260
00:14:56,596 --> 00:14:59,497
I mean, county court's in
westlake outside of the dome.

261
00:14:59,499 --> 00:15:01,933
We bring them in, and
then we figure it out.

262
00:15:01,935 --> 00:15:04,569
Dundees can't just walk
free after killing rose.

263
00:15:06,505 --> 00:15:08,573
Or what they were
gonna do to angie.

264
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:13,278
Wait, angie was attacked?

265
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:14,679
Just so you know, she's okay.

266
00:15:16,382 --> 00:15:18,449
They were gonna rape her.

267
00:15:20,452 --> 00:15:23,254
Barbie stopped them,
but then they got away.

268
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:29,527
Yeah, they won't
get away this time.

269
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:36,234
Can you go faster?

270
00:15:36,236 --> 00:15:37,335
It's just a few more blocks.

271
00:15:37,337 --> 00:15:39,337
What the hell is this?

272
00:15:42,408 --> 00:15:43,975
Sorry, I got to...

273
00:15:43,977 --> 00:15:44,943
nobody move!

274
00:15:44,945 --> 00:15:47,211
Or I'll blow your head off!

275
00:15:47,213 --> 00:15:48,680
my god, what do we do?

276
00:15:48,682 --> 00:15:51,215
We do exactly what they say.

277
00:15:51,217 --> 00:15:52,350
Shut up!

278
00:16:06,298 --> 00:16:07,498
You got it?

279
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:11,169
I can't believe
we're being gas-jacked.

280
00:16:11,171 --> 00:16:14,138
Car's not nearly as useful
as the fuel.

281
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:16,441
Come on, hurry up!

282
00:16:16,443 --> 00:16:18,242
Waylon, it's going!
Move!

283
00:16:24,017 --> 00:16:25,249
Barbie:
Linda?

284
00:16:25,251 --> 00:16:27,051
Linda, it's barbie.

285
00:16:27,053 --> 00:16:28,152
I just tangled
with the dundees.

286
00:16:28,154 --> 00:16:30,321
Copy. Where?

287
00:16:30,323 --> 00:16:31,556
julia: Try and squeeze my hand.

288
00:16:34,461 --> 00:16:36,194
He's okay. No one's hurt.
He's okay.

289
00:16:36,196 --> 00:16:39,197
We're at town center.
They took off to the northwest.

290
00:16:39,199 --> 00:16:40,431
Linda: We're on it.
She's going into labor.

291
00:16:40,433 --> 00:16:42,033
We got to get her
to the clinic.

292
00:16:42,035 --> 00:16:43,401
Barbie: That's not
gonna happen.

293
00:16:43,403 --> 00:16:45,470
Just went by there.
It's closed.
My baby's coming!

294
00:16:45,472 --> 00:16:47,138
Alice.

295
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:48,239
She's a doctor.

296
00:16:48,241 --> 00:16:51,576
We got to go.
But this car's not
going anywhere now.

297
00:16:51,578 --> 00:16:53,211
Then let's start
walking, come on.

298
00:16:53,213 --> 00:16:54,145
Get her out of
there, let's go.

299
00:16:54,147 --> 00:16:57,081
come on.

300
00:16:57,083 --> 00:16:58,449
Where do you think waylon
and clint are headed?

301
00:16:58,451 --> 00:17:00,485
Not much northwest of town.

302
00:17:00,487 --> 00:17:02,420
Except that salvage yard.

303
00:17:03,489 --> 00:17:04,589
What, you never played

304
00:17:04,591 --> 00:17:06,090
Hide and go seek
there as a kid?

305
00:17:06,092 --> 00:17:07,792
It's got lots
of old buildings.

306
00:17:07,794 --> 00:17:09,494
No one around.

307
00:17:09,496 --> 00:17:11,362
If they're on the run,
they're probably there.

308
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:13,398
It's worth a shot.
Yeah.

309
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,433
Let's go kick their teeth in.

310
00:17:15,435 --> 00:17:17,101
Like hell.

311
00:17:17,103 --> 00:17:19,170
We're gonna arrest them and
read them their rights.

312
00:17:19,172 --> 00:17:20,238
What, seriously?

313
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:23,808
You only use that gun if
your life is in danger.

314
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:24,809
Do you understand?

315
00:17:24,811 --> 00:17:26,110
Yeah, I got it.

316
00:17:26,112 --> 00:17:28,179
Whatever you say, sheriff.

317
00:17:31,251 --> 00:17:33,184
Do you think we're
getting closer?

318
00:17:33,186 --> 00:17:35,119
About five miles
from the wall.

319
00:17:35,121 --> 00:17:37,188
We've been going
perfectly southwest.

320
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:38,356
Shouldn't be too far now.

321
00:17:38,358 --> 00:17:40,091
If we ever
get out of here,

322
00:17:40,093 --> 00:17:41,325
You should seriously
consider a career

323
00:17:41,327 --> 00:17:44,629
Me and ben mapped
the dome on day one.

324
00:17:44,631 --> 00:17:48,099
Lucky I paid attention
in trig class.

325
00:17:48,101 --> 00:17:51,102
If we turn it off,
we can get my mom more insulin.

326
00:17:51,104 --> 00:17:52,370
H-how is she?

327
00:17:52,372 --> 00:17:55,473
She's good, but we're
gonna need more.

328
00:17:56,642 --> 00:17:58,409
Joe?

329
00:17:58,411 --> 00:18:00,478
Do you ever wonder
why it picked us?

330
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:04,215
Sure, but I'm mainly
just glad it did.

331
00:18:04,217 --> 00:18:07,351
Excuse me?

332
00:18:07,353 --> 00:18:10,121
I mean, it's weird
and it's scary,

333
00:18:10,123 --> 00:18:13,424
But it's the first time anything
like this has happened on earth.

334
00:18:13,426 --> 00:18:14,559
That's awesome...

335
00:18:14,561 --> 00:18:18,196
In the true "awe"
sense of awesome.

336
00:18:18,198 --> 00:18:22,100
Uh, not to mention,
if it hadn't come down,

337
00:18:22,102 --> 00:18:25,236
I might not have met you.

338
00:18:27,707 --> 00:18:29,240
What's his problem?

339
00:18:29,242 --> 00:18:30,575
Truman!

340
00:18:30,577 --> 00:18:33,277
Are you okay?

341
00:18:33,279 --> 00:18:36,347
Truman?

342
00:18:39,119 --> 00:18:40,685
Truman!

343
00:18:40,687 --> 00:18:42,120
He thinks something's wrong.

344
00:18:42,122 --> 00:18:44,188
Should we go back, too?

345
00:18:46,225 --> 00:18:47,859
We can't stop now.

346
00:18:47,861 --> 00:18:49,861
We're close.

347
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:06,144
Man, I never buried
anyone before.

348
00:19:06,146 --> 00:19:07,345
That was messed up.

349
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:09,714
I mean it was nice.

350
00:19:09,716 --> 00:19:11,282
It was nice of you
to bury rose.

351
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:15,720
I never appreciated her.

352
00:19:15,722 --> 00:19:17,622
I...

353
00:19:17,624 --> 00:19:21,659
Was always too busy wishing
that I was somewhere else.

354
00:19:23,595 --> 00:19:24,829
Someone else.

355
00:19:24,831 --> 00:19:27,865
We got to clean this place up.

356
00:19:27,867 --> 00:19:29,934
Why don't you go see if
you can find us a mop.

357
00:19:52,324 --> 00:19:54,926
What happened to you?

358
00:19:54,928 --> 00:19:58,462
People making trouble
for themselves.

359
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:02,767
I need a drink.

360
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:10,374
Ben:
Hell yeah!

361
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:11,275
Chug!

362
00:20:12,411 --> 00:20:13,911
Didn't know
you had company, angie.

363
00:20:13,913 --> 00:20:15,379
Ben:
Ben drake, sir.

364
00:20:15,381 --> 00:20:16,881
We met at one of junior's games.

365
00:20:16,883 --> 00:20:18,683
You been talking about junior?

366
00:20:18,685 --> 00:20:19,750
Angie:
No.

367
00:20:26,658 --> 00:20:28,392
Clean this blood up.

368
00:20:42,374 --> 00:20:44,308
Babe, I told you,

369
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:46,377
I'm feeling much better.

370
00:20:46,379 --> 00:20:48,312
For now.

371
00:20:48,314 --> 00:20:51,549
I just don't want to act sick
until I am sick.

372
00:20:51,551 --> 00:20:52,683
Honey...
Please?

373
00:20:52,685 --> 00:20:55,419
Your insulin has been
so irregular.

374
00:20:55,421 --> 00:20:57,555
It has to be messing with you.

375
00:20:57,557 --> 00:21:02,994
I'm telling you,
I don't need this.

376
00:21:02,996 --> 00:21:05,863
Okay then, badass.

377
00:21:05,865 --> 00:21:07,932
Get up and dance.

378
00:21:10,469 --> 00:21:12,536
I want to.

379
00:21:17,876 --> 00:21:21,846
♪ no time

380
00:21:30,522 --> 00:21:33,891
♪ no time

381
00:21:33,893 --> 00:21:37,061
I'm sorry.

382
00:21:38,797 --> 00:21:40,798
For what?

383
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:42,366
For bringing us here.

384
00:21:42,368 --> 00:21:45,536
For insisting that norrie
be sent to that program.

385
00:21:45,538 --> 00:21:46,837
I insisted, too.

386
00:21:46,839 --> 00:21:50,007
And I would
follow you anywhere.

387
00:21:50,009 --> 00:21:52,543
It is no one's fault.

388
00:22:12,030 --> 00:22:14,031
julia:
Alice?

389
00:22:14,033 --> 00:22:16,033
It's my neighbor harriet.

390
00:22:16,035 --> 00:22:17,568
She's in labor
a month early.

391
00:22:17,570 --> 00:22:19,870
let's get her
on the couch.

392
00:22:19,872 --> 00:22:21,105
Oh...

393
00:22:21,107 --> 00:22:22,373
All right,
nice and...

394
00:22:22,375 --> 00:22:23,374
Nice and slow.

395
00:22:23,376 --> 00:22:27,578
I'm not leaving.
...And you are
gonna be just fine.

396
00:22:27,580 --> 00:22:31,082
Actually, you're gonna have the
first baby born inside the dome.

397
00:22:35,954 --> 00:22:38,622
Oh, my god.

398
00:22:38,624 --> 00:22:40,558
The hair's standing up
on my arms.

399
00:22:42,994 --> 00:22:44,528
And there it is.

400
00:22:44,530 --> 00:22:47,531
Norrie:
What the hell is that?

401
00:22:55,540 --> 00:22:56,640
It shocked me.

402
00:23:11,423 --> 00:23:13,391
You've got to be
kidding me.

403
00:23:13,393 --> 00:23:16,961
I think there's
something inside.

404
00:23:46,658 --> 00:23:49,126
ten centimeters.
It's almost time to push.

405
00:23:49,128 --> 00:23:52,463
I can't do this
without my husband.

406
00:23:52,465 --> 00:23:54,598
I can't.
Harriet.
Harriet, listen to me.

407
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:56,467
I can't do this.
This happens
every day.

408
00:23:56,469 --> 00:23:57,902
You can do this.

409
00:23:57,904 --> 00:23:59,737
This is not
every day, alice.

410
00:23:59,739 --> 00:24:02,106
This isn't right...

411
00:24:02,108 --> 00:24:06,210
...Bringing someone
into a world like this.

412
00:24:08,514 --> 00:24:11,449
Harriet, you are gonna
be a wonderful mother.

413
00:24:11,451 --> 00:24:13,517
Do you remember
when we first met?

414
00:24:13,519 --> 00:24:15,619
You showed me the sonogram, and
you couldn't contain yourself.

415
00:24:15,621 --> 00:24:19,523
There's no hope
with people behaving this way.

416
00:24:19,525 --> 00:24:22,760
And it's only gonna
get worse, isn't it?

417
00:24:22,762 --> 00:24:25,229
With all of us trapped
under this thing? Isn't it?

418
00:24:25,231 --> 00:24:26,931
Julia:
You don't know that.
Okay, harriet, harriet, harriet.

419
00:24:26,933 --> 00:24:27,998
Look at me.
Look at me.

420
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:31,535
Right? Some people,
they're always gonna show up.

421
00:24:31,537 --> 00:24:32,670
Now, we're here.

422
00:24:32,672 --> 00:24:34,038
All right?
We're not going anywhere,

423
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:36,507
But I'm gonna need you
to show up, too.

424
00:24:36,509 --> 00:24:37,775
- Okay?
- okay.

425
00:24:37,777 --> 00:24:39,043
Yeah?

426
00:24:39,045 --> 00:24:40,778
Okay.
Will you hold my hand?

427
00:24:40,780 --> 00:24:42,146
Listen, I got you. Okay?

428
00:24:42,148 --> 00:24:44,515
We all do.

429
00:24:44,517 --> 00:24:47,151
Alice:
Harriet, it's time
to push, on three.

430
00:24:47,153 --> 00:24:49,253
You can do this,
harriet. One...

431
00:24:49,255 --> 00:24:50,254
two...

432
00:24:50,256 --> 00:24:51,722
Three!

433
00:24:56,062 --> 00:24:58,128
Ollie:
Hey, jimmy.

434
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:01,131
I hear you had
a little run-in

435
00:25:01,133 --> 00:25:03,601
With the new security guard
at your old propane warehouse.

436
00:25:05,271 --> 00:25:08,706
Well, I hate to see
my old friend sittin' here,

437
00:25:08,708 --> 00:25:11,075
Licking his wounds
like a fat-ass cat.

438
00:25:11,077 --> 00:25:13,143
So I'll be brief.

439
00:25:16,715 --> 00:25:20,084
Earlier, you said we
should be working together.

440
00:25:20,086 --> 00:25:22,820
But you see,
I got the well.

441
00:25:22,822 --> 00:25:24,288
And unless I'm wrong,

442
00:25:24,290 --> 00:25:26,524
I got more crops
than you townies,

443
00:25:26,526 --> 00:25:28,626
And now I got
the propane.

444
00:25:28,628 --> 00:25:31,829
So unless you want
your beloved chester's mill

445
00:25:31,831 --> 00:25:34,298
To starve to death...

446
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:36,033
You'll toe the line.

447
00:25:40,171 --> 00:25:43,040
You see, it's my turn
to have my sweaty hand

448
00:25:43,042 --> 00:25:45,309
Wrapped around this town's neck.

449
00:25:45,311 --> 00:25:47,678
So from now on,

450
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,847
When I say "jump,"

451
00:25:49,849 --> 00:25:52,182
You say, "how high?"

452
00:25:53,752 --> 00:25:57,721
Didn't I say it was
a nice new dawn this morning?

453
00:26:18,343 --> 00:26:20,644
I don't see anybody, do you?

454
00:26:20,646 --> 00:26:22,279
What are you so scared of?

455
00:26:22,281 --> 00:26:24,114
Uh, the guy that kicked
your ass yesterday.

456
00:26:24,116 --> 00:26:25,816
Almost did it
again today.

457
00:26:25,818 --> 00:26:27,751
I think he's a deputy.

458
00:26:27,753 --> 00:26:29,787
You know he's gonna tell linda.
You know, they ought

459
00:26:29,789 --> 00:26:31,655
To worry about us,
not the other way around.

460
00:26:31,657 --> 00:26:34,158
Whole town's
falling apart, clint.

461
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:37,161
There's a lot of good
opportunities, going forward.

462
00:26:37,163 --> 00:26:38,295
Waylon.

463
00:26:38,297 --> 00:26:39,830
There's somebody on your side.

464
00:26:47,205 --> 00:26:49,306
Damn, you're stupid, clint.

465
00:26:49,308 --> 00:26:52,109
Drop 'em and put your hands
where I can see them!

466
00:26:52,111 --> 00:26:53,177
Do what he says.

467
00:26:53,179 --> 00:26:55,279
Now!

468
00:26:57,215 --> 00:26:59,183
Put your hands
behind your head.

469
00:27:02,654 --> 00:27:04,154
You're both
under arrest

470
00:27:04,156 --> 00:27:06,190
For the murder
of rose twitchell.

471
00:27:06,192 --> 00:27:07,758
You have the right
to remain silent.

472
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:08,792
Anything you say

473
00:27:08,794 --> 00:27:10,694
Can and will
be held against...

474
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:33,150
Please.

475
00:27:33,152 --> 00:27:35,319
I'll go quietly, please.

476
00:27:35,321 --> 00:27:36,687
I'll go peacefully.

477
00:27:36,689 --> 00:27:38,822
Please...

478
00:27:45,930 --> 00:27:47,297
Junior...

479
00:27:48,833 --> 00:27:50,401
Got him.

480
00:27:54,839 --> 00:27:57,908
Maybe it's the generator
that created the whole dome.

481
00:28:01,379 --> 00:28:03,347
Open.

482
00:28:03,349 --> 00:28:06,350
Open and turn off.

483
00:28:06,352 --> 00:28:07,351
End program.

484
00:28:07,353 --> 00:28:08,719
It's not working, joe.

485
00:28:08,721 --> 00:28:10,320
You think?

486
00:28:12,991 --> 00:28:14,291
Hello.

487
00:28:14,293 --> 00:28:16,794
Begin communication.

488
00:28:16,796 --> 00:28:18,328
Who are <i>you</i> talking to?

489
00:28:20,432 --> 00:28:21,432
Hey, you!

490
00:28:21,434 --> 00:28:23,801
Initiate communication!

491
00:28:23,803 --> 00:28:25,369
Maybe it doesn't like
being yelled at.

492
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:29,173
What if we ask nicely?

493
00:28:29,175 --> 00:28:31,341
The big dome responded when
we both touched it together,

494
00:28:31,343 --> 00:28:32,876
And made the radio
work again.

495
00:28:37,783 --> 00:28:39,316
Okay.

496
00:28:40,285 --> 00:28:41,852
Outer space thing,

497
00:28:41,854 --> 00:28:43,787
We would like it
very much

498
00:28:43,789 --> 00:28:45,422
If we could just
talk to you.

499
00:28:45,424 --> 00:28:46,924
And...
Norrie.

500
00:28:54,332 --> 00:28:55,833
Mom?

501
00:29:07,412 --> 00:29:09,413
I need to find my mom.

502
00:29:10,882 --> 00:29:12,816
Come on!

503
00:29:12,818 --> 00:29:14,051
that's it!
That's it!

504
00:29:14,053 --> 00:29:15,919
that's great.

505
00:29:15,921 --> 00:29:16,920
Okay.

506
00:29:18,357 --> 00:29:19,389
Uh-oh.

507
00:29:19,391 --> 00:29:20,824
What?
Is something wrong

508
00:29:20,826 --> 00:29:21,925
With my baby?

509
00:29:21,927 --> 00:29:23,293
No, you're fine,
sweetheart.

510
00:29:23,295 --> 00:29:24,928
Something's wrong.

511
00:29:24,930 --> 00:29:26,830
Alice?
Uh...

512
00:29:28,334 --> 00:29:29,333
What's happening?

513
00:29:29,335 --> 00:29:30,534
Nothing.
Everything's fine, okay?

514
00:29:30,536 --> 00:29:33,537
No, I...
yes.
Yes, all right?

515
00:29:33,539 --> 00:29:36,039
One... Here we go. One...
It hurts so much.

516
00:29:36,041 --> 00:29:37,541
...Two, three.
Push!

517
00:29:44,983 --> 00:29:46,984
♪

518
00:30:13,946 --> 00:30:16,847
No! No!

519
00:30:37,369 --> 00:30:40,003
Okay, okay, okay, okay.
Head's out.

520
00:30:40,005 --> 00:30:41,572
I don't... Is this...
Is everything all right here?

521
00:30:41,574 --> 00:30:43,407
No. No, no, no.

522
00:30:43,409 --> 00:30:45,409
You can't.
I have to.

523
00:30:45,411 --> 00:30:46,410
Okay...

524
00:30:46,412 --> 00:30:48,612
I need you to stop pushing.

525
00:30:48,614 --> 00:30:50,414
Uh...

526
00:30:50,416 --> 00:30:52,883
Harriet, you need
to stop pushing.

527
00:30:52,885 --> 00:30:53,917
What?
I need you
to stop pushing.

528
00:30:53,919 --> 00:30:55,419
The cord...

529
00:30:55,421 --> 00:30:59,022
okay, well, you're gonna
